CatDescriptText: Nancy Davis, 504 Lowell Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 23, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "In the coming November elections, do you think voters should elect another Democratic Governor or change to a Republican?" answer reads: "Lawrence is a Democrat. (Democratic nominee).  I like him.  Therefore I think that we should have another Democrat."
TitMainTitle: Unknown woman and Nancy Davis, with Pittsburgh Courier reporter George Barbour on left, standing on Fifth Avenue, Oakland
